WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.000
Thermal response test: a borehole, grout, fluid, and surrounding ground.

00:02.000 --> 00:04.000
Early heating contains information about the grout's heat capacity.

00:04.000 --> 00:06.000
The short-time predictions separate across the three analytical treatments.

00:06.000 --> 00:08.000
The composite cylindrical source retains grout storage in the inner boundary.

00:08.000 --> 00:10.000
The reported field comparison gives the CCS the lowest RMSE.

00:10.000 --> 00:12.000
Grout capacity matters earlier; ground conductivity matters later.

00:12.000 --> 00:14.000
The reported uncertainty analysis identifies a transition near 42 hours.

00:14.000 --> 00:16.300
Practical stability is reported around 48 to 50 hours for this study.

00:16.300 --> 00:18.134
The duration result is source-conditioned, not a universal TRT rule.
